  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Various strategies have been proposed to prevent or mitigate the effects of&#xD;
      ischemia-reperfusion injury following the use of tourniquets in orthopedic surgery cases. One&#xD;
      of them is applying &quot;remote ischemic preconditioning.&quot; This randomized controlled trial is&#xD;
      planned to evaluate the effectiveness of remote ischemic preconditioning in preventing&#xD;
      tourniquet-induced ischemia-reperfusion injury in total knee arthroscopy with dynamic&#xD;
      thiol-disulfide homeostasis.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
